{
  "stem": "27409.8",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Liaison with the Jewish population and to organize their aliyah.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Because I brought, over the border, people from Hungary, which they couldn't speak a word Romanian, but I was there from representative of the International Red Cross, too, had official papers to bring them.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I brought them over the border as this-- this money, and this, and help-- joint help with money.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We left Romania on 24th of December, 1946.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We had-- I had to organize trains.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Romania was divided in eight groups.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And from-- we had to bring-- it was the-- the Jewish [NON-ENGLISH], or answer to the exodus.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "As they send the people back to Germany.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You know this.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we had two ships, [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They were banana boats.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We had to prepare them.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And they arrived in Burgas where they were prepared for the aliyah.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "This ship would have been only for 2,000, 2,200 soldiers in wartime, and we put on these two ships 17,000 people, from Bulgaria and from Romania, mostly.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And we had to organize the train.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "My part was southern Transylvania, that is on this side of the Carpathian.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Organize the train.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Organize one-way passports from the Romanian authority.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "It was all bought.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And we went up there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Women and children, I had about 1,700 people on my train.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "In every train carriage I had one of my boys, who was trained, and which listen to me, they got on [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "There were women and children.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "There were problems, they were not luxury trains.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "It was very good [INAUDIBLE] again.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "But we went over.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Went first, because they under the pressure of the British authorities there went-- didn't let the ship stay, so they went over to Bulgaria, Burgas.",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
